---
title: "Gobi 65 (Crispy Cauliflower 65)"
slug: "gobi-65-recipe-cauliflower-65-fry"
description: "Crispy fried cauliflower tossed in a spicy South Indian tempering with curry leaves."
cuisine: "South Indian"
prepMinutes: 10
cookMinutes: 30
servings: "4 servings"
diet: ["vegan"]
tags: ["gobi 65", "cauliflower fry", "starter"]
publishedAt: "2026-01-29"

ingredients:
  - "1 medium cauliflower, cut into florets"
  - "¼ cup plain flour"
  - "¼ cup rice flour or cornflour"
  - "1½ tsp ginger garlic paste"
  - "½ tsp garam masala"
  - "¼ tsp black pepper"
  - "1 tsp chilli powder"
  - "Salt to taste"
  - "¼ cup water (for batter)"
  - "Oil for frying"
  - "2 green chillies, slit"
  - "3 garlic cloves, chopped"
  - "½ tsp cumin seeds"
  - "Curry leaves"
  - "½ tsp chilli powder (tempering)"
  - "¼ tsp garam masala (tempering)"
  - "2 tbsp vegan yogurt or vinegar-water mix"

instructions:
  - "Blanch cauliflower briefly in hot water, rinse and drain well."
  - "Mix flour, rice flour, spices, ginger garlic paste and water to make a thick batter."
  - "Coat cauliflower and deep fry until golden and crispy."
  - "Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds, garlic, chillies and curry leaves."
  - "Add chilli powder, garam masala and yogurt mixture. Cook until thick."
  - "Add fried cauliflower and toss on high heat for 2–3 minutes."
  - "Serve hot as a starter or snack."

---

## Gobi 65

A popular South Indian restaurant snack with crispy texture and bold flavour.

### Tips
- Bake or air fry instead of deep frying for a lighter version.
- Serve with mint chutney or ketchup.